29  import java.nio.charset.Charset;
30  import java.nio.charset.CharsetDecoder;
31  import java.nio.charset.CharsetEncoder;
32  import java.nio.charset.CharacterCodingException;
33  import sun.nio.cs.HistoricallyNamedCharset;

36  
37  public class IBM950_OLD extends Charset implements HistoricallyNamedCharset
38  {
39      public IBM950_OLD() {
40          super("x-IBM950-Old", null);
41      }
42  
43      public String historicalName() {
44          return "Cp950";
45      }
46  
47      public boolean contains(Charset cs) {
48          return ((cs.name().equals("US-ASCII"))
49                  || (cs instanceof IBM950));
50      }
51  
52      public CharsetDecoder newDecoder() {
53          return new Decoder(this);
54      }
55  
56      public CharsetEncoder newEncoder() {
57          return new Encoder(this);
58      }
59  
60      public short[] getDecoderIndex1() {
61          return Decoder.index1;
62  
63      }
64      public String getDecoderIndex2() {
65          return Decoder.index2;
66  
67      }
68      public short[] getEncoderIndex1() {
69          return Encoder.index1;
70  
71      }
72      public String getEncoderIndex2() {
73          return Encoder.index2;
74  
75      }
76      public String getEncoderIndex2a() {
77          return Encoder.index2a;
78  
79      }

81      private static class Decoder extends DBCS_IBM_ASCII_Decoder {
82          public Decoder(Charset cs) {
83                  super(cs);
84                  super.mask1 = 0xFFE0;
85                  super.mask2 = 0x001F;
86                  super.shift = 5;
87                  super.leadByte = this.leadByte;
88                  super.singleByteToChar = this.singleByteToChar;
89                  super.index1 = this.index1;
90                  super.index2 = this.index2;
91          }
